<subSubSection lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1446,2011]" lastBlockId="24.[151,1436,151,536]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="23" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1770,1795]" pageId="23" pageNumber="74">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sacco" box="[323,472,1771,1795]" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" refString="Sacco, F. (1899) I Molluschi dei terreni terziarii del Piemonti e della Liguria. Parte XXVII (Unionidae, Carditidae, Astartidae, Crassatellidae, Lasaeidae, Galeommidae, Cardiidae, Limnocardiidae e Chamidae). Carlo Clausen, Torino, 102 pp." type="book" year="1899">Sacco (1899)</bibRefCitation>
erected the genus in order to separate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. de C. Sowerby" authorityYear="1825" box="[911,1151,1770,1795]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Venericardia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="scalaris">
<emphasis box="[911,1151,1770,1795]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="74">Venericardia scalaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authority="Dall, 1903" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1903" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Miodontiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1222,1373,1770,1795]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="74">Miodontiscus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dall" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" refString="Dall, W. H. (1903) Contributions to the Tertiary fauna of Florida with special reference to the Silex Beds of the Caloosahatchie River. Part IV. Transactions of the Wagner Free Institute of Science of Philadelphia, 3 (4), 1219 - 1654." type="journal article" year="1903">Dall, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="de Gregorio, 1885" authorityName="de Gregorio" authorityYear="1885" box="[270,576,1806,1831]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Coripia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[270,357,1807,1830]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="74">Coripia</emphasis>
de 
<bibRefCitation author="Gregorio" box="[401,576,1806,1831]" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" refString="de Gregorio, A. (1885) Appunti intorno ad alcune Cardite viventi e fossili. Bulletino della Societa Malacologica Italiana, 10, 146 - 156." type="journal article" year="1885">Gregorio, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; which comprise very small-sized Cenozoic carditids from 
<collectingCountry box="[1251,1304,1806,1831]" name="Italy" pageId="23" pageNumber="74">Italy</collectingCountry>
. Sacco also indicated that 
<taxonomicName box="[322,483,1842,1867]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Scalaricardita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[322,483,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="74">Scalaricardita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a smaller shell with less circular outline, less convex dorsal margin, more pronounced radial ribs with subrectangular instead of subrounded nodes, provided with smaller and less curved right middle tooth and less curved right posterior tooth. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sacco" box="[777,925,1915,1939]" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" refString="Sacco, F. (1899) I Molluschi dei terreni terziarii del Piemonti e della Liguria. Parte XXVII (Unionidae, Carditidae, Astartidae, Crassatellidae, Lasaeidae, Galeommidae, Cardiidae, Limnocardiidae e Chamidae). Carlo Clausen, Torino, 102 pp." type="book" year="1899">Sacco (1899)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. de C. Sowerby" authorityYear="1825" box="[1106,1222,1914,1939]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Venericardia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="scalaris">
<emphasis box="[1106,1222,1914,1939]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="74">V. scalaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Conrad, 1867" authorityName="Conrad" authorityYear="1867" box="[151,453,1950,1975]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Cyclocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,288,1950,1975]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="74">Cyclocardia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Conrad" box="[298,453,1950,1975]" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" refString="Conrad, T. A. (1867) Description of a new genus of Astartidae. American Journal of Conchology, 3, 191." type="journal article" year="1867">Conrad, 1867</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by similarities in outline and shell sculpture, and later 
<bibRefCitation author="Dall" box="[1098,1224,1950,1975]" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" refString="Dall, W. H. (1902) Synopsis of the Carditacea and of the American species. Proceedings of the Academy National Science of Philadelphia, 54, 696 - 716." type="journal article" year="1902">Dall (1902</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dall" box="[1239,1296,1951,1975]" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" refString="Dall, W. H. (1903) Contributions to the Tertiary fauna of Florida with special reference to the Silex Beds of the Caloosahatchie River. Part IV. Transactions of the Wagner Free Institute of Science of Philadelphia, 3 (4), 1219 - 1654." type="journal article" year="1903">1903</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Thiele" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" refString="Thiele, G. (1935) Handbuch der systematischen Weichtierkunde. Teil 3. ConchBooks, Harxheim, 244 pp. [pp. 779 - 1022]" type="book chapter" year="1935">Thiele (1935)</bibRefCitation>
suggested a possible synonymy between 
<taxonomicName box="[704,864,1986,2011]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Scalaricardita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[704,864,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="74">Scalaricardita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Conrad" authorityYear="1867" box="[924,1061,1986,2011]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Cyclocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[924,1061,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="74">Cyclocardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[1077,1238,1986,2011]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Scalaricardita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="23" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1077,1238,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="74">Scalaricardita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1903" box="[214,365,151,176]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Miodontiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="24" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,365,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="75">Miodontiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Gregorio" authorityYear="1885" box="[424,511,152,175]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Coripia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="24" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[424,511,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="75">Coripia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by having a more rounded shell with subcentrally placed umbo, less radial ribs with subrectangular nodes and narrower intercostal spaces.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="75" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="24" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName box="[199,360,223,248]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Scalaricardita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="24" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,360,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="75">Scalaricardita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Conrad, 1867" authorityName="Conrad" authorityYear="1867" box="[509,807,223,248]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Pleuromeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="24" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[509,646,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="75">Pleuromeris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Conrad" box="[654,807,223,248]" pageId="24" pageNumber="75" refString="Conrad, T. A. (1867) Description of a new genus of Astartidae. American Journal of Conchology, 3, 191." type="journal article" year="1867">Conrad, 1867</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(type species 
<taxonomicName authority="Conrad, 1867" authorityName="Conrad" authorityYear="1867" box="[969,1313,223,248]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Pleuromeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="24" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="decemcostata">
<emphasis box="[969,1149,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="75">P. decemcostata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Conrad" box="[1157,1313,223,248]" pageId="24" pageNumber="75" refString="Conrad, T. A. (1867) Description of a new genus of Astartidae. American Journal of Conchology, 3, 191." type="journal article" year="1867">Conrad, 1867</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; Pliocene– Pleistocene of USA) by having a less triangular outline and a higher number of radial ribs separated by narrower intercostal spaces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="24" pageNumber="75">
The genus is represented in the Miocene and Pliocene of Europe by the type species (
<bibRefCitation author="Sacco" box="[1177,1313,332,356]" pageId="24" pageNumber="75" refString="Sacco, F. (1899) I Molluschi dei terreni terziarii del Piemonti e della Liguria. Parte XXVII (Unionidae, Carditidae, Astartidae, Crassatellidae, Lasaeidae, Galeommidae, Cardiidae, Limnocardiidae e Chamidae). Carlo Clausen, Torino, 102 pp." type="book" year="1899">Sacco 1899</bibRefCitation>
; Glibert &amp; Van der 
<bibRefCitation author="Poel" box="[244,359,367,392]" pageId="24" pageNumber="75" refString="Glibert, M. &amp; Van der Poel, L. (1970) Les Bivalvia fossiles du Cenozoique etranger des collections de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique. Part VI. Memoires Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, 84, 1 - 185." type="journal article" year="1970">Poel 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Raffi" box="[371,556,367,392]" pageId="24" pageNumber="75" refString="Raffi, S., Stanley, S. &amp; Marasti, R. (1985) Biogeographic patterns and Plio-Pleistocene extinction of Bivalvia in the Mediterranean and Southern North Sea. Paleobiology, 11 (4), 368 - 388. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / s 0094837300011684" type="journal article" year="1985">
Raffi 
<emphasis box="[434,491,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
1985
